name: 詹娜·克雷
introduction: Jenna Kray (she/they) is an American actor and singer. She received a BFA in Theatre Performance and a minor in Media Studies at VCUarts. She additionally studied at The University of Edinburgh and worked at the International Fringe Festival. She can be seen on shows such as Mare of Easttown (HBO), Billions (Showtime), New Amsterdam (NBC) , Blue Bloods (CBS), and in Saturday Night Live (NBC) digital shorts. Her feature film work debut was in Luckiest Girl Alive (Netflix) based on the book of the same name. Jenna has narrated the novel 'Old Enough' by Haley Jakobson published by Penguin Randomhouse. They are based in New York City.
